Title: Searchforuhuru
Creator: Searchforuhuru
Description: The Vision is to build a bridge between Africa & her children of the diaspora. Oluse Afara ,which translates to bridge maker in Yoruba, is a title which was given to Dynast Amir which encompasses the work that he is doing. The title of Oluse Afara isn’t only limited to Dynast Amir, but to all of those whom are on a similar path. Building this bridge is the key to a much deeper mission. Dynast wants the diaspora to also invest in the people, the culture, help assist in building the infrastructure, and bring business development to Africa.

Title: African Docs

Description: Welcome to African Docs. In this YouTube channel, we share everything educational about Africa and Africans, both home and abroad. Our objective is to promote “a people-oriented leadership” and to inspire the leaders of tomorrow, both in Africa and among different African communities in the diaspora. Title: Reel Black
Creator: Reel Black
Description: Reelblack's mission is to educate, entertain, enlighten and empower people through Black film. Since 2007, we have been capturing the New Black Film Revolution through interviews with the filmmakers, actors and musicians that make up the movement. In addition to our original content, we dig through archives to share video and music relevant to these conversations. Founder MIKE D. is a graduate of both NYU and The American Film Institute.

Title: The New Africa Channel
Creator: The New Africa Channel
Description: The New Africa Channel is Africa’s most comprehensive and number video channel for mega construction projects, development, technology, environmental, business opportunities, trending issues, and more.  Our work aims to connect Africans in Africa and in the Diaspora with the rest of the world. No matter where we come from, we're all connected to Africa. At The New Africa Channel, our viewing audience guides the direction of our platform, and we always want to present quality content that meets our viewer's needs.

Title: KueliMika
Creator: KueliMika
Description: Hi! On this channel we analyze and review certain African historical and social knowledge taught to us by either our schools, our parents, our society, or the media. We do all that by remaining as objective as possible and as academically  sourced as possible. Therefore, we welcome you to join our channel, and participate in this journey to a better knowledge and  understanding of our past and our current society!

Title: African Diaspora News Channel
Creator: African Diaspora News Channel
Description: African Diaspora News Channel presents international news, social commentary, travel, and health. We're committed to reporting truthful and accurate news. Our viewers expect and love the "tell it like it is" style of reporting. We're dedicated to bringing stories that spark conversation and topics that aren't comfortable in a politically correct world. We will say what we believe and stand against propaganda. You can expect a balanced opinion in our news commentaries. We believe our viewing audience guides the direction of our platform.

Our content includes; - Development Projects in Africa. - Business Opportunities in Africa. - Real Estate Investment  - Entrepreneurship advice from prominent businessmen. -Economies of African nations - History & Lifestyle of African Cities & its people.  For Business inquiries, takedowns, and other requests. Contact us through africaguide54@gmail.com.
